window-dialogues desired...
-

This Library is in two parts organised, around as well as beginners as\than too advanced
 just become to. The  basic version you find in the  file
GFA_FLY4.LST. This routines contain\ed no window dialogues.

The  additional(ly) routines for window-dialogues you find inclusive of. Beispiellisting
in the  file WINDOW.LST. This routines are full compatible to the basic version,
merely the  procedures 'rsc_draw' and 'rsc_back' became extends\ed as well as some
other procedures added. This routines can for alternatively too
'normal' dialogues depict and comprise quasi the  basic version.

-
handling...
-

To program beginning should the  procedure

 rsc_init
 become called. You initializes\ed the  of the  RSC-routines need
global   variables. Some become from it in the interest of the clean
programming probable(ly) anyway of your program  needs:

 Ap_id& -> The  application-Id our program.
 Rsc_s&  -> AES-version
 rsc_mtsk! -> TRUE with Multitasking (MultiTOS , MAG!X, ...)
 rsc_vh& -> Handle of the Flydial-screen-Workstation.
 Planes& -> number Bitplanes.
 Deskx& -> sizes of the  Desktopbereiches...
 desky&
 deskw&
 deskh&

 -

The  Resource will(_be) with

 ~@rsc_load(file$,anz_trees&,popup&,menu&,alert&)

loaded and initializes\ed. 'file$' is on this occasion the  filename, 'anz_trees&' the 
number of the trees (with 0 starting). 'popup&' marks/ed the  Popup-tree (s.u.),
'menu&' the  Dropdown-menu tree and 'alert&' the  ALERT-Dialogue. Is it no 
this trees, so is in each case -1 to put.

The  Resource-Construction-Set INTERFACE offers the  tree-types ALERT and FREESTRING
 to. You hold (self) with the  initialization unfortunately not as 'real'
dialogues and have to from there separate become dealt with. This trees locate (self)
always imperative on the end a RSC-file and its Indexzhlung begins again with
0. 'rsc_load' contains already the  corresponding(ly) lines as\than REMs,that  you in the
need only auskommentieren have to. Nevertheless gives it with it Following to 
observe: The  passed over]-Variable 'alert&' must the  number of the  dialogues contain\ed,
the  direct(ly) before the  ALERT-or FREE-treess in the  Resource stands. With it should
it (self) normally around the  GFA_FLY4-particular Alert-Dialogue deal with. Should this
however not become employs\ed, satisfy it, here a empty Dialogue to insert.
The  Routine 'rsc_alert' may in this case natural(ly) never become called.

The  function supplies TRUE back, if the  Resource correct(ly) loaded became.

In this function become following global variables initializes\ed:

 Rsc_trees -> The  number of the object trees.
 Rsc_popup& -> The  Index of the  Popup-object tree.
 Rsc_menu& -> The  Index of the  Dropdown-menu tree.
 Rsc_alert -> The  Index of the  Alert-dialogues.

 Rscx&() -> The  coordinates of the dialogues, as it
 rscy&() of FORM_CENTER become delivered back.
 Rscw&()
 rsch&()

 rsc_adr%() -> The  addresses of the object trees.

 Rsc_handle%() -> Contains with a normal Dialogue the  address of the  buffered
 background, with a window-Dialogue the  FensterHandle.
 With this Variable will(_be) the  later too the 
 differentiation window dialogue<->normal Dialogue made.

Not direct(ly) in this function initializes\ed, but of the  routines other
still employed global Variaben are:

 Rsc_list$ -> Contains a list of the open dialogues in the MKI$()-format.
 See 'rsc_draw'.

 Rsc_ac_close& -> The  EXIT-Code with Eintreffen a AC_CLOSE-report.
 See 'employment in Accessories'.

 -

A Dialogue will(_be) with

 rsc_draw(tree_index&,window_flag%)

drawn. Window_flag% is a Bitflag,that  different options configures\ed.
 Hitherto covers\ed:

 Bit 0 -> window dialogue.
 Bit 1 -> close field (only with window dialogue)
 Bit 2 -> Dialogue immediately draw (only with window dialogues)

Is so Bit 0 placed, so will(_be) the  Dialogue in the window depicted, otherwise 
as\than normal Dialogue. In later case will(_be) after possibility the  
background buffered and the  address of the  buffer in rsc_handle%() saved.
As well will(_be) with WIND_UPDATE(BEG_UPDATE) of the screen for other applications
 closed.

Is Bit 1 placed, so receive the  window a close field. But caution: Only
the  first Dialogue a call-Hierarchie may a Closer possess, other 
can it to problems come! Until now contains this Library plain only modale
window dialogues.

Is Bit 2 placed, so will(_be) a window dialogue immediately by the 'rsc_draw'-call
drawn. Normally would the  eintreffende Redraw-report namely first
by the call of 'rsc_do' become evaluated.

With a window dialogue become all menu title until to the  first disabled.
Should no window more to the provision place, so will(_be) _always_ a normal
Dialogue employs\ed.

If a Dialogue never in the window should become depicted, you can it in the
RCS complete(ly)   free(ly) shape. If it but too (or always) in the window should become depicted,
valid it following to observe:
-It should a underlined title have. This title will(_be) namely as\than
 window title employs\ed, otherwise has the  window no title.
-The  first two lines of a dialogues become not in the window depicted, from there
 should it no objects except for the  Flugecke and the  Dialogtitel contain\ed!

In the  global   variables 'rsc_list$' will(_be) a list all opened dialogues 
mitgefhrt. With its help can too with low memory a Verstmmelung
of the  screen composition become prevents\ed, if several dialogues one on top of the other become called.
 As well relevant is this list by the call of the DateiauswahlBox
 over a Dialogue. Special to the this subject gives it in the  extended
version the  routines 'rsc_save_dialog' and 'rsc_restore_dialog'.

 -

The  processing of a dialogues results with

 rsc&=@rsc_do(tree&,next_obj&,popup&)

'tree&' marks/ed with it the  Index of the  Dialogbaumes, 'next_obj&' the  object, in 
that the  cursor to start stands (in the doubtful cases 0).

'rsc&' contains after the  End of the Dialogauswertung the  number of the  called
object. With a Double click to a TOUCHEXIT-object will(_be) analogous to the Original-FORM_DO
 the  15. Bit placed.

Exception: In the ACC-operation or as\than window dialogue with close field must the  Dialogue
immediately become leave, without that a special object called became. In
this case gives 'rsc_do' the  value of the variables 'rsc_ac_close&' back. From there
must with the  damage condition so if need be  too to this value become tested!
The  valid as said only for the  ACC-operation or if the  window dialogue a
Closer possesses\ed! Read you to it please too the  section 'employment in ACCs...'
against end (of)this text.

'popup&' is also a Rckgabevariable,that  only evaluated become must,
if a Popup-menu called became (s.u.).

With a window dialogue will(_be) from this Routine out the  procedure 

 message_eject(msg&,id&,len&,handle&,x&,y&,w&,h&)

called, if a window of the  program serves\ed became. With this procedure
should it (self) around your global evaluation of the Message-events deal with. You
gets the  complete(ly)  AES-Message-buffer pass/ed. The  likes to the  first 
look bertrieben and involved look, brings but several advantages.

The  'Top' of a particular window is during the  Dialogdurchfhrung not 
possible,that  window different programs can but in the  foreground become fetched.
Also the  Close of a particular window is not possible, there other
maybethe  rsc_do-Routine could become leave. The  could to weighty
problem take. Should you be sure(ly), that the  Close of a Hintergrundfensters
 with your program  no problems limited, you can it but nevertheless
 to allow.

Should you no further window in your program  employ, must natural(ly)
no 'message_eject'-procedure exist. The  corresponding(ly) lines
can then to REM become.

 -

The  Dialogue will(_be) with

 rsc_back(tree&)

from the screen removes\ed. With it will(_be) with a normal Dialogue of the buffered
background restores\ed and the  screen-block with WIND_UPDATE(END_UPDATE)
secured. With a window dialogue will(_be) the  window closed and the  menu title
 again callable  made(for).

 -

On the program end should

 rsc_exit
 become called. Here become the  requested memory areas released
and the  virtual Workstation closed.

 -

Still a word to this Library: All routines are very compresses\ed kept,
i.e. it became as possible a great deal of lines in _a_ procedure packed. That is normally
 no good style, in our cases but meaningful, with it the  overview
in the real(ly) program  not hinders\ed will(_be). The  routines are as\than 'Blackboxes'
 designs\ed, in that you normally anyway no look more throw
have to. Provided (that) you the  routines this Lib not change, can it later
simple(r) through updated versions become replaces\ed.

