-
Popup-menus...
-

All Popup-menus have to (self) in _a_ object tree locate, its number will(_be)
'rsc_load' to start pass/ed. The  father-object of a Popup-menus is a 
shaded Box,that  child-objects are from the type TEXT or STRING and have to in 
rising sequence be sorts\ed. Also the  individual Popups have to in
this form be sorts\ed.

A Popup-Button is a shades\ed Button. A possible(ly) Circlebutton
must Kindobjekt (of)this be Buttons.

Each Popup-Button will(_be) now a Popup-menu assigned,that  by the Click on
of the  Buttons appears. The  occurs/ed over the  extended object type. Here will(_be)
the  number of the  Popup-menus plus 30 entered. Wohlgemerkt, it goes here not
around the  object number, but around the  Index of the  Popup-menus referring to to the  tree,
in the  (self) the  menus locate. Contains it e.g. 3 menus, so go this numbers
of 1-3.

The  operation of a Popup-Buttons will(_be) automatic(ally) in the  rsc_do-Routine
deals/t with,that  yes as already well-known called will(_be):

 Rsc&=@rsc_do(tree&,popup&)

After the  Select of a menu item gives the  rsc_do-Routine as usual the 
object number of the  called object, in this case so of the  Popup-Buttons,
back. Additional contains the  Variable popup& the  Index of the  called
menu-entry. This can now evaluated become, must but not.

Popup-menus are too over the  keyboard controllable:

 Cursor high/down: Entry up/down.
 Esc/Undo : Bricht the  choice from.
 Return/Enter : Chooses a entry from.

A keyboard-operable String (s.o.) immediate before the  Popup activates\ed
also the  menu.

A Circlebutton can too over the  keyboard become serves\ed: Press you
to this <SHIFT> + <ALTERNATE> + <unterstr. Character> of the  vorstehenden Strings.

-
3D-display...
-

With the  FALCON-and MultiTOS  held a new Gestaltungsform moving in in the 
triste world of the dialogues: The  coloured 3D-display. The  OB_FLAGS 9 and 10 of a
object put with it firm, in what 3D-form it depicted will(_be). More detailed take out
 you please corresponding(ly) (MultiTOS -) documentations.

With it a userdefined object this Lib in 3D depicted will(_be), must also
Bit 9 and/or 10 in OB_FLAGS be placed. Out of optical(ly) grounds recommends it
(self) though, only Bit 10 to put. Otherwise would the  TOS a object with
additional(ly) 3D-effects provide\d,that  not absolute(ly) beautiful to look at are.

Over the  AES-function OBJC_SYSVAR will(_be) in 'rsc_load' the  colour of the 3D-objects
ascertains/ed and the  Assembler-INLINE pass/ed. Additional will(_be) a flag pass/ed,
 that the  3D-display global a-or switches off: Is it <>0, become so
objects three-dimensional drawn, provided (that) Bit 10 in OB_FLAGS is placed. Is
the  flag =0, so will(_be) no userdefined object in 3D depicted.

3D-display is present only from AES 3.40, i.e. to the  Falcon i.e.. under
MultiTOS  possible. In monochrome is general(ly) no 3D-display possible,that 
is simple\ly stethisch not justifiable.

