-
Goodies...
-

 -
 Goodie I
 -

In the  Assembler-INLINE is a special BITBLT integrates\ed,that  direct(ly)
can become called. It puts then a flexiblen replacement for GET/PUT
and too the  Basic-BITBLT on. Called will(_be) it with the  following parameters,
the  to them of the  Original BITBLT agree:

^C:Rsc_bitblt%(L:Qadr%,qw&,qh&,qr&,qp&,
 L:Zadr%,zw&,zh&,zr&,zp&,
 x&,y&,w&,h&,ax&,ay&,mod&)

qadr% address of the  source raster:
Qw& width in pixels
qh& height in pixels
qr& Rasterformat (0=Gerteabhng., 1=Standard)
qp& Bitplanes

zadr% address of the  Zielrasters:
Zw& width in pixels
zh& height in pixels
zr& Rasterformat (0=Gerteabhng., 1=Standard)
zp& Bitplanes

x&,y&,w&,h& To kopierender area
ax&,ay& Zielkoordinaten

mod& Kopiermodus (1,2,3,4)

For advanced: This function employs\ed the  VDI-Routine vrt_cpyfm()
i.e.. with same number Bitplanes automatic(ally) vro_cpyfm().

As well: The  extended routines (EXTENDED.LST) contain\ed the  procedures 
'rsc_get' and rsc_put',that  to base this function the  Basic-GET/PUT 
replace.

 -
 Goodie II
 -

Also in the  INLINE integrates\ed is a special OB_SPEC-Routine. This
gives for each object the  address back, to the  Textstring of the  object
stands. So can with the  function

 DEFFN rsc_text$(rsc_adr%,obj&)=CHAR{C:Rsc_obspec%(L:Rsc_adr%,obj&)}

simple\ly the  corresponding(ly) text become selected i.e.. with the  procedure

 PROCEDURE rsc_text(rsc_adr%,obj&,a$)
 CHAR{C:Rsc_obspec%(L:Rsc_adr%,obj&)}=a$
 RETURN

the  text become placed. A involved Distinguishs  after the  ObjektTyp
 drops\ed with it!

 -
 Goodie III
 -

To good last contains the  INLINE too still a Routine,that  a certain
Cookie searches and its value deliver back:

 Worth%=C:Rsc_cookie%(L:CVL("WINX")) ! Searches the  WINX-Cookie

Became the  Cookie not found, will(_be) 0 delivered back.

